# Code of Conduct

## Purpose

We are dedicated as a community to providing a welcoming and inclusive environment for everyone, regardless of background, identity, or experience. We value diversity, respect, and collaboration, and we are committed to fostering a space where all participants feel safe, respected, and valued.

## Scope

This code of conduct applies to all project spaces associated with **eWorker**, including but not limited to online forums, mailing lists, social media channels, events, and project communication platforms.

## Expected Behavior

We expect all participants to:

- Treat others with kindness, empathy, and respect.
- Listen actively and communicate constructively.
- Be inclusive and welcoming to people of all backgrounds and identities.
- Exercise patience and understanding in interactions with others.
- Respect differing viewpoints and experiences.
- Refrain from engaging in behavior that could be considered harassing, intimidating, or disrespectful.

## Unacceptable Behavior

Examples of unacceptable behavior include, but are not limited to:

- Harassment, discrimination, or bullying based on race, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation, disability, religion, or any other characteristic.
- Personal attacks, insults, or derogatory language directed at individuals or groups.
- Threats of violence or harm.
- Deliberate disruption of discussions or activities.
- Unwelcome sexual advances or inappropriate behavior.
- Sharing of sensitive or confidential information without consent.
- Any other conduct that violates the principles of respect, inclusivity, and collaboration.

## Reporting Process

If you experience or witness behavior that violates this code of conduct, please report it to [Dean](https://github.com/codebydean). All reports will be handled confidentially and with respect for the privacy of the individuals involved. We are committed to addressing and resolving reported incidents appropriately.

## Enforcement Actions

Participants who engage in behavior that violates this code of conduct may be subject to disciplinary action, including but not limited to warnings, temporary or permanent bans from project spaces, and removal from leadership roles or other project responsibilities. Decisions regarding enforcement actions will be made by the project leader based on the severity and impact of the behavior.

## Community Responsibilities

We encourage all contributors to:

- Familiarize themselves with this code of conduct and abide by its principles.
- Support individuals who report violations of the code of conduct and offer assistance as needed.
- Foster a culture of inclusivity, respect, and collaboration within the community.
- Communicate concerns or feedback about the code of conduct or community environment to [Dean](https://github.com/codebydean).

## Acknowledgment

By participating in **eWorker**, you agree to uphold the principles and standards outlined in this code of conduct and to adhere to the reporting and enforcement processes described herein.

## Contact Information

For questions, concerns, or reports related to this code of conduct, please contact [Dean](https://github.com/codebydean) via LinkedIn or X.
